casebody.data:
[Grafton,

December, 1882.] State v. Cashman. A. 8. Batchellor, solicitor, for the state. Drew, Jordan Carpenter, Bingha/m, Aldrich $ Bemich, and Bingham Sf Mitchell, for the respondent.

Indictment for embezzlement. Facts agreed. Counsel disagreeing as to the question intended to be raised, no decision was . rendered, and the case was discharged.

Allen, J., did not sit: the others concurred.
